# Cursor Workflow Commands

## Quick Commands (use in Cursor Chat/Agent)

### /scaffold

"Run the rapid-scaffold skill: create `frontend/` (Next.js) and `backend/` (FastAPI) per monorepo layout; follow root `.env.example`."

### /deploy

"Deploy using the deploy-free-hosting skill: Vercel for `frontend/` (Root Directory `frontend`); deploy `backend/` to Railway, Render, or Fly; set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` and CORS."

### /fix

"Run builds for both packages and fix errors: `cd frontend && npm run build`; `cd backend` and run tests or `python -m compileall` / your FastAPI check; fix issues one by one."

### /test-flow

"Open the browser and test: signup -> login -> add income/expense -> assign category -> confirm landing stats and dashboard charts -> edit/delete transaction -> logout (frontend + FastAPI + Supabase)."

### /design

"Follow docs/DESIGN.md and the design-aperture skill when implementing or refactoring UI in frontend/."

### /document

"Update docs/ai-workflow.md with all AI interactions from this session"

### /status

"Show project status: what's working, what's broken, what's left to build (frontend/, backend/, Supabase, deploys)."

### /emergency

"I have limited time left. Prioritize: minimum working demo — frontend on Vercel, API reachable, one CRUD path, auth working — defer polish."

## Keyboard Shortcut Reminders

- `Ctrl+K` - Quick AI edit in file
- `Ctrl+L` - Open Chat panel
- `Ctrl+I` - Inline AI suggestion
- `Ctrl+Shift+I` - Open Agent mode (Composer)
- `Tab` - Accept AI suggestion
